push and insert will never (re)allocate if the reported capacity is sufficient. push and insertwill (re)allocate if len==capacity. Bulk insertion methods may reallocate, even when not necessary.

То есть заявленная емкость полностью точна, и на нее можно положиться. Его можно даже использовать для ручного освобождения памяти, выделенной Vec , если это необходимо. trans-unit.source: Eq and PartialEq are traits that allow you to define total and partial equality between values, respectively. Implementing them overloads the == and != operators.

Error::source() is generally used when errors cross "abstraction boundaries". If one module must report an error that is caused by an error from a lower-level module, it can allow accessing that error via Error::source(). This makes it possible for the high-level module to provide its own errors while also revealing some of the implementation for debugging via source chains.
